original_font_information.description: Le Monde Livre Classic Std, designed by Jean Francois Porchez in 1994, is a serif typeface available in 6 weights.  More than 1600 glyphs including full latin support, small caps, 4 set of figures, various set of additional figures, superiors, ligatures, alternates, swashes and dingbats. OpenType features and extended kerning (380 000 pairs) are included. Specific OpenType features are: Stylist set 1: ornaments, Stylistic set 2: swashes, Stylistic set 3: Swashes + contextual alternates, Stylistic set 4: stylistic alternates, Stylistic set 5: traditional ligatures, Stylistic set 6: additional ligatures
